        "title": "fix(qa): reduce WhatsApp live RTT setup cost",
        "body": "Summary\n- Register WhatsApp through a narrow runtime setter entrypoint so gateway startup no longer imports the broad WhatsApp runtime barrel before live message handling.\n- Add WhatsApp live QA retry handling for logged-out Convex credentials; stale leases stay held while the lane tries alternate pooled credentials.\n- Add a maintainer-role workflow input for WhatsApp Convex leases, and switch QA gateway-child readiness from `config.get` to lightweight `health` RPC to avoid loading the full config schema during startup checks.\n- Keep the existing WhatsApp RTT instrumentation, heap snapshots, gateway traces, and changelog coverage on this branch.\n\nVerification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/index.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-runtime-api-guardrails.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/whatsapp-live.runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/gateway-child.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs -c .oxlintrc.json --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/whatsapp/index.ts extensions/whatsapp/index.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/runtime-setter-api.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-runtime-api-guardrails.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs -c .oxlintrc.json --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/whatsapp-live.runtime.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/whatsapp-live.runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs -c .oxlintrc.json --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/qa-lab/src/gateway-child.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/gateway-child.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Testbox-through-Crabbox changed gate: `tbx_01ks94abkaf4rjwh7hemswwb6t`, Actions run `26318665070`, `pnpm check:changed` at `8f1403f35b3` passed.\n\nLive evidence\n- `26315828755` at `c2bad2a4099`: WhatsApp job failed before RTT; CI Convex credential fingerprint `6b2d34243bac` was logged out (`401 Unauthorized`).\n- `26316577807` at `9897bcfe79a`: maintainer role failed before RTT because `OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SECRET_MAINTAINER` is not configured.\n- `26317166666` at `57a09eee274`: retry path held the logged-out CI credential and attempted another lease; broker exhausted after 360000ms, proving the CI WhatsApp pool currently has no alternate healthy credential.\n- Repo secret listing confirms `OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SECRET_CI` and `OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SITE_URL` exist, but `OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SECRET_MAINTAINER` is absent.\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp live QA now avoids one eager runtime import path, reports stale Convex WhatsApp credentials without silently reacquiring the same row, skips full config-schema work for gateway-child RPC readiness, and preserves retry auth directories across successful alternate credential startup.\nReal environment tested: GitHub Actions live WhatsApp Convex QA on Blacksmith runners, Testbox-through-Crabbox changed gate, plus targeted local Vitest/oxlint/diff checks in the branch worktree.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `qa-live-transports-convex.yml` with `ref=whatsapp-rtt-leak`, `whatsapp_scenario=whatsapp-canary`, `whatsapp_credential_role=ci`, `matrix_profile=fast`; Testbox-through-Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` on `whatsapp-rtt-leak` after deepening `origin/main`.\nEvidence after fix: stale credential fingerprint `6b2d34243bac` is identified and held; alternate acquisition exhausts, so current live RTT proof is blocked by credential pool state rather than an unclassified harness failure; `pnpm check:changed` is green at `8f1403f35b3`.\nObserved result after fix: branch improves startup/QA hygiene and credential diagnosis, but it does not yet prove the WhatsApp RTT target; the only CI WhatsApp credential is logged out.\nWhat was not tested: a successful live WhatsApp RTT run after `70b607800bb`; current Convex credential state blocks that proof.\n",
